ological model described by a rotationally symmetric 2D Gaussian model at\n99.7% confidence level. Our results exclude the radio lobes ($\\approx$30 kpc)\nas the principal component of the VHE gamma-ray emission from the low state of\nM87. The gamma-ray emission is compatible with a single emission region at the\nradio core of M87. These results, with the help of two multiple-component\nmodels, constrain the maximum cosmic-ray to thermal pressure ratio\n$X_{{CR,max.}}$$\\lesssim$$0.32$ and the total energy in cosmic-ray protons\n(CRp) to $U_{CR}$$\\lesssim$5$\\times10^{58}$ erg in the inner 20kpc of the Virgo\nCluster for an assumed CRp power-law distribution in momentum with spectral\nindex $\\alpha_{p}$=2.1.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 May 2023 16:59:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-17"}
